acy. She shows that, while at first glance, ballroom presents a highly gendered face with men leading and women following, dancing also transgresses gender.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aBallroom dancingxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814722664.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814722855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814722855/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles